# Architecture Plan

## Project Shape

This is a Vite + React + TypeScript frontend app that will become a small live
clock with a persisted 12-hour/24-hour display preference.

Keep the source tree shallow and conventional:

- `src/main.tsx`: React root render and global stylesheet import.
- `src/App.tsx`: Page composition only; it should wire hooks to components.
- `src/index.css`: Tailwind entry point and global base styles after issue #3.
- `src/hooks/useCurrentTime.ts`: Live `Date` state updated once per second.
- `src/hooks/useFormatPref.ts`: Persisted time-format preference state.
- `src/components/ClockDisplay.tsx`: Presentational time/date display.
- `src/components/FormatToggle.tsx`: Presentational 12h/24h toggle control.
- `src/types/time.ts`: Shared `TimeFormat` type if both hook and components need
  the same exported type.
- `src/test/` or colocated `*.test.ts(x)`: Unit tests, chosen consistently when
  test tooling is added.
- `tests/e2e/`: Playwright smoke tests.

## Shared Types

Use a narrow shared type for the preference:

```ts
export type TimeFormat = '12h' | '24h'
```

The format hook should expose `[format, setFormat]` or an object with equivalent
values. Prefer the tuple only if it stays idiomatic and obvious at call sites;
otherwise use `{ format, setFormat }` for clarity.

## Issue Dependencies

- #3 Tailwind CSS is the styling foundation for #7, #8, and #9.
- #4 linting/formatting can be done after the scaffold and before broader edits.
- #5 `useCurrentTime` is required by #7 and #10.
- #6 `useFormatPref` is required by #7, #8, and #10.
- #7 `ClockDisplay` depends on #3, #5, and #6.
- #8 `FormatToggle` depends on #3 and #6.
- #9 `App.tsx` composes #7 and #8.
- #10 hook unit tests depend on #5 and #6.
- #11 component unit tests depend on #7 and #8.
- #12 Playwright smoke test depends on the assembled app from #9 and should run
  after the unit-test tooling is settled.

## Key Design Decisions

- Keep time formatting inside `ClockDisplay` unless another consumer appears.
  Use `Intl.DateTimeFormat` instead of manual string assembly for locale-aware
  date and time output.
- Default to `24h` when `localStorage` is missing, unavailable, or contains an
  invalid value.
- Guard browser-only storage access so tests and non-browser execution do not
  fail unexpectedly.
- Have `useCurrentTime` clean up its interval on unmount and use fake timers in
  tests to verify both ticking and cleanup behavior.
- Make `FormatToggle` controlled: it receives `format` and `setFormat`/`onChange`
  from the hook owner and does not read storage directly.
- Keep `App.tsx` thin: call hooks, pass props, and own the responsive page
  layout.
- Add Tailwind with minimal custom configuration first. Remove or neutralize the
  Vite starter CSS when the clock UI is assembled so old scaffold styles do not
  leak into the final page.
- Use Vitest + React Testing Library for unit/component tests and Playwright for
  the end-to-end smoke test.
